Text.SourceString: Good morning, <PlayerName>$Player</>! You seemed to like my cooking, so...um, I decided to make something for you.//I hope that's okay...
Text.LocalizedString: Good morning, <PlayerName>$Player</>! You seemed to like my cooking, so...um, I decided to make something for you.//I hope that's okay...

Text.SourceString: I made breakfast today. I hope you like it, baby...
Text.LocalizedString: I made breakfast today. I hope you like it, baby...

Text.SourceString: Um, I noticed the crops are doing well...I-I mean, not that you need me to tell you that...//<portrait=happy>I just thought you'd like to know...
Text.LocalizedString: Um, I noticed the crops are doing well...I-I mean, not that you need me to tell you that...//<portrait=happy>I just thought you'd like to know...

Text.SourceString: I saw a few wild rabbits in our farm this morning. They seemed harmless but...//I'll keep an eye on them just in case they try to nibble our crops...
Text.LocalizedString: I saw a few wild rabbits in our farm this morning. They seemed harmless but...//I'll keep an eye on them just in case they try to nibble our crops...

Text.SourceString: The animals...they looked a bit distressed during the storm. I hope it didn't scare them too much.
Text.LocalizedString: The animals...they looked a bit distressed during the storm. I hope it didn't scare them too much.

Text.SourceString: I've been reading this book about astronomy...//I'd love to show you some constellations, if you'd like...
Text.LocalizedString: I've been reading this book about astronomy...//I'd love to show you some constellations, if you'd like...

Text.SourceString: I found a quiet spot by the river, perfect for reading. Maybe...maybe we could go together sometime?
Text.LocalizedString: I found a quiet spot by the river, perfect for reading. Maybe...maybe we could go together sometime?

Text.SourceString: I heard some chatter about <NpcName>Antonio</> at Sam's...but you know how I am with gossip, babe.//<portrait=normal>Let's just enjoy our peace here...
Text.LocalizedString: I heard some chatter about <NpcName>Antonio</> at Sam's...but you know how I am with gossip, babe.//<portrait=normal>Let's just enjoy our peace here...

Text.SourceString: Remember when you gave me my first gift? I was so nervous...haha...//It was the happiest day of my life.
Text.LocalizedString: Remember when you gave me my first gift? I was so nervous...haha...//It was the happiest day of my life.

Text.SourceString: Before you, I was always the shy one, the one everyone overlooked.//But you...you saw me. And I'll always be grateful for that.
Text.LocalizedString: Before you, I was always the shy one, the one everyone overlooked.//But you...you saw me. And I'll always be grateful for that.

Text.SourceString: I read a book on gemstones... Maybe it could help you with mining? I can show you if you want...
Text.LocalizedString: I read a book on gemstones... Maybe it could help you with mining? I can show you if you want...

Text.SourceString: I know you're excited for the Harvest Festival...but remember not to push yourself too hard, okay?//<portrait=concerned>I don't want you to get too tired, baby.
Text.LocalizedString: I know you're excited for the Harvest Festival...but remember not to push yourself too hard, okay?//<portrait=concerned>I don't want you to get too tired, baby.

Text.SourceString: Um, there's a festival coming up soon, isn't there, baby?//<portrait=surprised>Oh yes...the Spooky Festival! Will you be dressing up this year?
Text.LocalizedString: Um, there's a festival coming up soon, isn't there, baby?//<portrait=surprised>Oh yes...the Spooky Festival! Will you be dressing up this year?

Text.SourceString: You're really talented, you know? The way you manage the farm...it's truly impressive.
Text.LocalizedString: You're really talented, you know? The way you manage the farm...it's truly impressive.

Text.SourceString: I'm lucky to have you by my side.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm lucky to have you by my side.

Text.SourceString: When I'm with you, I feel... safe. Warm. Happy. I... um... I love you, and I hope you know that.
Text.LocalizedString: When I'm with you, I feel... safe. Warm. Happy. I... um... I love you, and I hope you know that.

Text.SourceString: I don't know how to put this into words, but... I love you.
Text.LocalizedString: I don't know how to put this into words, but... I love you.

Text.SourceString: You've brought so much light into my life, thank you, <PlayerName>$Player</>...
Text.LocalizedString: You've brought so much light into my life, thank you, <PlayerName>$Player</>...

Text.SourceString: The Cherry Blossom Festival is tomorrow, isn't it? I'm... um, I'm looking forward to it.//I wonder if <NpcName>Pablo</> is going...
Text.LocalizedString: The Cherry Blossom Festival is tomorrow, isn't it? I'm... um, I'm looking forward to it.//I wonder if <NpcName>Pablo</> is going...

Text.SourceString: I, um, checked the boats for the Tree Planting Festival yesterday... Everything seemed to be in order, so... so there's no need to worry.
Text.LocalizedString: I, um, checked the boats for the Tree Planting Festival yesterday... Everything seemed to be in order, so... so there's no need to worry.

Text.SourceString: Should we wear hats tomorrow, baby?//It might get really hot... I'll bring one for you, just to be safe...
Text.LocalizedString: Should we wear hats tomorrow, baby?//It might get really hot... I'll bring one for you, just to be safe...

Text.SourceString: I, um, I changed the light bulbs in our bedroom, <PlayerName>$Player</>. Everything should be working fine now.
Text.LocalizedString: I, um, I changed the light bulbs in our bedroom, <PlayerName>$Player</>. Everything should be working fine now.

Text.SourceString: I'm planning to clean the house this week...//You don't need to worry about it, okay? I've got this.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm planning to clean the house this week...//You don't need to worry about it, okay? I've got this.

Text.SourceString: I've prepared your sweaters for Winter, babe. They should be on the top drawer.//You, um, won't have to search for them.
Text.LocalizedString: I've prepared your sweaters for Winter, babe. They should be on the top drawer.//You, um, won't have to search for them.

Text.SourceString: Um, do you know where my beanies might be, <PlayerName>$Player</>?//I was thinking of wearing one this Winter. Could you help me look?
Text.LocalizedString: Um, do you know where my beanies might be, <PlayerName>$Player</>?//I was thinking of wearing one this Winter. Could you help me look?

Text.SourceString: You've been working so hard.//Maybe I could give you a massage later, if...if that's okay with you?
Text.LocalizedString: You've been working so hard.//Maybe I could give you a massage later, if...if that's okay with you?

Text.SourceString: Do we have any plans for today?
Text.LocalizedString: Do we have any plans for today?

Text.SourceString: Is there anything you'd like me to pick up from Sam's, <PlayerName>$Player</>? I might drop by the clinic later for my flu shot.
Text.LocalizedString: Is there anything you'd like me to pick up from Sam's, <PlayerName>$Player</>? I might drop by the clinic later for my flu shot.

Text.SourceString: Um...where did we keep the stone cleaners, babe?//I couldn't find them under the sink. Are are we out?
Text.LocalizedString: Um...where did we keep the stone cleaners, babe?//I couldn't find them under the sink. Are are we out?

Text.SourceString: I need to tidy up the cemetery soon... The moss is getting a bit wild.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to tidy up the cemetery soon... The moss is getting a bit wild.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, when I look out over our farm, I think about our old days, sitting on the porch...imagining growing old together.//It makes me feel...so grateful.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, when I look out over our farm, I think about our old days, sitting on the porch...imagining growing old together.//It makes me feel...so grateful.

Text.SourceString: Finding peace used to be hard for me at the house...with the loud furnace, being next to the school and all.//But here, it's so...quiet and peaceful.
Text.LocalizedString: Finding peace used to be hard for me at the house...with the loud furnace, being next to the school and all.//But here, it's so...quiet and peaceful.

Text.SourceString: I should, um, probably drop by the inn soon. Check up on things, see if anything needs fixing...
Text.LocalizedString: I should, um, probably drop by the inn soon. Check up on things, see if anything needs fixing...

Text.SourceString: Would you like to come with me?
Text.LocalizedString: Would you like to come with me?

Text.SourceString: Do you feel like watching some TV, <PlayerName>$Player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you feel like watching some TV, <PlayerName>$Player</>?

Text.SourceString: How was your day today? I'd love to hear all about it.
Text.LocalizedString: How was your day today? I'd love to hear all about it.

Text.SourceString: I could use an early night tonight... I feel a bit tired, babe.
Text.LocalizedString: I could use an early night tonight... I feel a bit tired, babe.

Text.SourceString: I...um, I've missed you, baby... Would you mind if we cuddle for a bit?
Text.LocalizedString: I...um, I've missed you, baby... Would you mind if we cuddle for a bit?

Text.SourceString: Would it be okay if I kissed you?
Text.LocalizedString: Would it be okay if I kissed you?

Text.SourceString: If you want to spend the day cuddling in bed, I'd be up for that... With the snow outside and all, I wasn't sure if you'd want to go out...
Text.LocalizedString: If you want to spend the day cuddling in bed, I'd be up for that... With the snow outside and all, I wasn't sure if you'd want to go out...

Text.SourceString: I hope you have a good day, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: I hope you have a good day, okay?

Text.SourceString: I'll be right here if you need anything, alright? I'm just going to do some dishes for a bit.
Text.LocalizedString: I'll be right here if you need anything, alright? I'm just going to do some dishes for a bit.

Text.SourceString: The shop gets a lot of work from the town.//You know, like, um, setting up decorations and stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: The shop gets a lot of work from the town.//You know, like, um, setting up decorations and stuff.

Text.SourceString: I don't mind, really...cleaning up the town. It's where I grew up.//This whole town is my playground, and I want to take care of it.
Text.LocalizedString: I don't mind, really...cleaning up the town. It's where I grew up.//This whole town is my playground, and I want to take care of it.

Text.SourceString: The cemetery is so quiet. And the lake too.//It’s a great place to read horror novels.
Text.LocalizedString: The cemetery is so quiet. And the lake too.//It’s a great place to read horror novels.

Text.SourceString: We could...umm, maybe read some books there? If you like that kinda thing.
Text.LocalizedString: We could...umm, maybe read some books there? If you like that kinda thing.

Text.SourceString: The shop gets its ore from that cavern up north, past the forest.//If you can't find the ore you need, uh...well, just keep digging a bit more, maybe?
Text.LocalizedString: The shop gets its ore from that cavern up north, past the forest.//If you can't find the ore you need, uh...well, just keep digging a bit more, maybe?

Text.SourceString: When you upgrade your tools, they’ll change color a bit.//It depends on the material.
Text.LocalizedString: When you upgrade your tools, they’ll change color a bit.//It depends on the material.

Text.SourceString: Don’t be worried, it's totally normal. I'll keep an eye on it for you.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t be worried, it's totally normal. I'll keep an eye on it for you.

Text.SourceString: There’s nothing I like more than a good horror movie.//The ones that keep you guessing and a bit jumpy.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s nothing I like more than a good horror movie.//The ones that keep you guessing and a bit jumpy.

Text.SourceString: Okay, maybe trying out a new weapon. That's exciting too.
Text.LocalizedString: Okay, maybe trying out a new weapon. That's exciting too.

Text.SourceString: Every time I stop by to see <NPCName>Pablo</>, he's in the garage.//He seems to <Italic>always</> be calibrating his TV.
Text.LocalizedString: Every time I stop by to see <NPCName>Pablo</>, he's in the garage.//He seems to <Italic>always</> be calibrating his TV.

Text.SourceString: The air down at the beach, it's, um, different. More salty.//<portrait=annoyed>And kinda sticky, too.
Text.LocalizedString: The air down at the beach, it's, um, different. More salty.//<portrait=annoyed>And kinda sticky, too.

Text.SourceString: The shop's getting real busy, baby. Makes me think... We might need a bigger place.//Or maybe just some better tools.
Text.LocalizedString: The shop's getting real busy, baby. Makes me think... We might need a bigger place.//Or maybe just some better tools.

Text.SourceString: I use my forge, my bellows, and my own two hands.//Sometimes, though, I wish I had a little extra help.
Text.LocalizedString: I use my forge, my bellows, and my own two hands.//Sometimes, though, I wish I had a little extra help.

Text.SourceString: Aside from <NPCName>Pablo</>, of course.//He's really, um, great.
Text.LocalizedString: Aside from <NPCName>Pablo</>, of course.//He's really, um, great.

Text.SourceString: There’s more ore than what you find down in the cavern. Some impressive stuff.//Some might call it, um, mythical…//<portrait=annoyed>Most of it probably just old tales, though.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s more ore than what you find down in the cavern. Some impressive stuff.//Some might call it, um, mythical…//<portrait=annoyed>Most of it probably just old tales, though.

Text.SourceString: But tales start somewhere, right? There could be a sliver of truth in ’em.
Text.LocalizedString: But tales start somewhere, right? There could be a sliver of truth in ’em.

Text.SourceString: I gave carpentry a shot, but it wasn't my thing.//<portrait=concerned>I can handle little things, maybe fix up a cabinet, but a whole house is too big for me. Uh...sorry, babe...ha ha...um.
Text.LocalizedString: I gave carpentry a shot, but it wasn't my thing.//<portrait=concerned>I can handle little things, maybe fix up a cabinet, but a whole house is too big for me. Uh...sorry, babe...ha ha...um.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Joko</> and <NPCName>Dinda</> are top-notch carpenters, anyway.//We can always ask for their help.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Joko</> and <NPCName>Dinda</> are top-notch carpenters, anyway.//We can always ask for their help.

Text.SourceString: I like making weapons more than upgrading tools.//<portrait=happy>The shop doesn't have a lot of resources for making weapons, but that's not gonna, um, stop me.
Text.LocalizedString: I like making weapons more than upgrading tools.//<portrait=happy>The shop doesn't have a lot of resources for making weapons, but that's not gonna, um, stop me.

Text.SourceString: Our farm is a nice place to live. Just far enough from the town.//<portrait=annoyed>The woodland, though…ugh, it was way too close to everyone for me.
Text.LocalizedString: Our farm is a nice place to live. Just far enough from the town.//<portrait=annoyed>The woodland, though…ugh, it was way too close to everyone for me.

Text.SourceString: Argh.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, hey, baby! Didn’t see you there.
Text.LocalizedString: Argh.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, hey, baby! Didn’t see you there.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Valentina</> is a great kid. I feel like <NPCName>Antonio</> is a bit too hard on her sometimes.//But I’m not her parent, so…
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Valentina</> is a great kid. I feel like <NPCName>Antonio</> is a bit too hard on her sometimes.//But I’m not her parent, so…

Text.SourceString: I shouldn't meddle in other people's business, right, baby?//<portrait=concerned>What do you think? Should I say something...or no?
Text.LocalizedString: I shouldn't meddle in other people's business, right, baby?//<portrait=concerned>What do you think? Should I say something...or no?

Text.SourceString: Used to sting a bit when people were shocked that me and <NPCName>Pablo</> are brothers. But I'm okay now...I mean, I do take after Mom and he, uh, looks more like Dad.
Text.LocalizedString: Used to sting a bit when people were shocked that me and <NPCName>Pablo</> are brothers. But I'm okay now...I mean, I do take after Mom and he, uh, looks more like Dad.

Text.SourceString: So, I guess it's not too surprising people get a bit shocked.
Text.LocalizedString: So, I guess it's not too surprising people get a bit shocked.

Text.SourceString: I smelt ore all day sometimes. *sighs* So, please don’t mind my dirty clothes.
Text.LocalizedString: I smelt ore all day sometimes. *sighs* So, please don’t mind my dirty clothes.

Text.SourceString: It's easy to lose track of time. Smelting ore is such a, um...mundane job.//My body kind of goes into autopilot.
Text.LocalizedString: It's easy to lose track of time. Smelting ore is such a, um...mundane job.//My body kind of goes into autopilot.

Text.SourceString: Is it hot outside, or is it just me?
Text.LocalizedString: Is it hot outside, or is it just me?

Text.SourceString: Summer feels a bit too much for me. I, um, prefer Winter.//<portrait=concerned>Uh…or maybe Fall.
Text.LocalizedString: Summer feels a bit too much for me. I, um, prefer Winter.//<portrait=concerned>Uh…or maybe Fall.

Text.SourceString: I’m looking forward to the hot pot at the Cherry Blossom Festival.//<portrait=annoyed>Not looking forward to fishing the vegetables out of my portion, though…
Text.LocalizedString: I’m looking forward to the hot pot at the Cherry Blossom Festival.//<portrait=annoyed>Not looking forward to fishing the vegetables out of my portion, though…

Text.SourceString: The cherry blossoms are looking really nice this year.
Text.LocalizedString: The cherry blossoms are looking really nice this year.

Text.SourceString: I wish Winter could be longer, but new horror films are usually released in Fall… So, that’s something to look forward to.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish Winter could be longer, but new horror films are usually released in Fall… So, that’s something to look forward to.

Text.SourceString: I just want to stay outside all day…
Text.LocalizedString: I just want to stay outside all day…

Text.SourceString: Working in front of the furnace in Summer is…intense. //I can handle it in other seasons, but Summer is just too much.
Text.LocalizedString: Working in front of the furnace in Summer is…intense. //I can handle it in other seasons, but Summer is just too much.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Pablo</> keeps asking me to go to the Tavern, but I always tell him I've made plans with you. He he!//<portrait=normal>I'm not really a fan of the Tavern.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Pablo</> keeps asking me to go to the Tavern, but I always tell him I've made plans with you. He he!//<portrait=normal>I'm not really a fan of the Tavern.

Text.SourceString: The bugs are making music out here.//Just last night, I could hear those little bugs chirping right outside our window. It's...um, it's kinda nice...
Text.LocalizedString: The bugs are making music out here.//Just last night, I could hear those little bugs chirping right outside our window. It's...um, it's kinda nice...

Text.SourceString: I’m looking forward to <NPCName>Betty’s</> homemade mooncakes. They’re always the highlight of Fall for me.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m looking forward to <NPCName>Betty’s</> homemade mooncakes. They’re always the highlight of Fall for me.

Text.SourceString: I wonder what horror films are coming out this Fall.//I like the ones with jump scares. Just nice classic horror films with ghosts.//<portrait=concerned>Um…
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder what horror films are coming out this Fall.//I like the ones with jump scares. Just nice classic horror films with ghosts.//<portrait=concerned>Um…

Text.SourceString: I wonder what Beluga Bay will be showing at this year’s Harvest Festival…
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder what Beluga Bay will be showing at this year’s Harvest Festival…

Text.SourceString: Fall might be my favorite season, I guess.//I’m lucky to live here. It's easy to just go out and enjoy nature whenever I want to.
Text.LocalizedString: Fall might be my favorite season, I guess.//I’m lucky to live here. It's easy to just go out and enjoy nature whenever I want to.

Text.SourceString: Winter is nice… I like it.
Text.LocalizedString: Winter is nice… I like it.

Text.SourceString: Um, I was thinking about making ramen for dinner tonight...and, um, I think we might actually have all the ingredients we need.
Text.LocalizedString: Um, I was thinking about making ramen for dinner tonight...and, um, I think we might actually have all the ingredients we need.

Text.SourceString: If I get too hot at the shop, I just step outside and let the cold air cool me down. // Don't worry, okay? I'll be fine.
Text.LocalizedString: If I get too hot at the shop, I just step outside and let the cold air cool me down. // Don't worry, okay? I'll be fine.

Text.SourceString: Are you warm? Make sure to stay warm, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you warm? Make sure to stay warm, okay?

Text.SourceString: This Winter is a little dry.//My hands hurt if I wash them too much. But it’s nothing unbearable. It’s okay…
Text.LocalizedString: This Winter is a little dry.//My hands hurt if I wash them too much. But it’s nothing unbearable. It’s okay…

Text.SourceString: Winter coats are, um, hard to wash. They're very thick. Take ages to dry.
Text.LocalizedString: Winter coats are, um, hard to wash. They're very thick. Take ages to dry.

Text.SourceString: I like the cold wind. It feels good against my face after a whole day in front of the hot furnace.
Text.LocalizedString: I like the cold wind. It feels good against my face after a whole day in front of the hot furnace.

Text.SourceString: For some reason, mosquitos don’t bite me. Isn’t that weird?
Text.LocalizedString: For some reason, mosquitos don’t bite me. Isn’t that weird?

Text.SourceString: I brought some edamame for <NPCName>Valentina</> yesterday. I keep forgetting she hates it.//I hope she doesn’t hate me now.
Text.LocalizedString: I brought some edamame for <NPCName>Valentina</> yesterday. I keep forgetting she hates it.//I hope she doesn’t hate me now.

Text.SourceString: Eating something cold like cold fish or ice cream would be good right about now.
Text.LocalizedString: Eating something cold like cold fish or ice cream would be good right about now.

Text.SourceString: The majority of the trash here drifted in from the sea. Can you imagine what it’s like where this trash came from?
Text.LocalizedString: The majority of the trash here drifted in from the sea. Can you imagine what it’s like where this trash came from?

Text.SourceString: Um, I, uh, need to go to the clinic this week... My rash is acting up again. I think the sweat might be triggering it.
Text.LocalizedString: Um, I, uh, need to go to the clinic this week... My rash is acting up again. I think the sweat might be triggering it.

Text.SourceString: Heh heh… What? You look happy today.//It kind of makes me happy to see.
Text.LocalizedString: Heh heh… What? You look happy today.//It kind of makes me happy to see.

Text.SourceString: Today is the last day of Summer, yet the heat doesn’t want to let up.
Text.LocalizedString: Today is the last day of Summer, yet the heat doesn’t want to let up.

Text.SourceString: I like the cold wind. It feels good against my face after a whole day in front of the hot furnace.
Text.LocalizedString: I like the cold wind. It feels good against my face after a whole day in front of the hot furnace.

Text.SourceString: I’m kind of nervous about <NPCName>Bree</>'s dinner party tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m kind of nervous about <NPCName>Bree</>'s dinner party tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: I’m afraid I might say the wrong thing and ruin people’s dinner.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m afraid I might say the wrong thing and ruin people’s dinner.

Text.SourceString: I hope it starts raining soon.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope it starts raining soon.

Text.SourceString: The walking path could do with a good rinse.
Text.LocalizedString: The walking path could do with a good rinse.

Text.SourceString: The rain makes for some relaxing white noise in the background, don’t you think?
Text.LocalizedString: The rain makes for some relaxing white noise in the background, don’t you think?

Text.SourceString: *yawns*
Text.LocalizedString: *yawns*

Text.SourceString: Um, I feel a bit weird talking here.
Text.LocalizedString: Um, I feel a bit weird talking here.

Text.SourceString: The rain makes for some relaxing white noise in the background, don’t you think?
Text.LocalizedString: The rain makes for some relaxing white noise in the background, don’t you think?

Text.SourceString: *yawns*
Text.LocalizedString: *yawns*

Text.SourceString: Oh no! I need to dry off my boots. Mud everywhere!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh no! I need to dry off my boots. Mud everywhere!

Text.SourceString: Oh well.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh well.

Text.SourceString: It’s, um, storming outside.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s, um, storming outside.

Text.SourceString: It’s, um, still storming outside.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s, um, still storming outside.

Text.SourceString: The rain is relaxing, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: The rain is relaxing, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: Walking's a bit tough when it's raining, though.
Text.LocalizedString: Walking's a bit tough when it's raining, though.

Text.SourceString: The snow helps me build up a resistance to cold weather.
Text.LocalizedString: The snow helps me build up a resistance to cold weather.

Text.SourceString: You can find all sorts of shiny things in the cavern.//If you dig deep enough, there are plenty of diamonds and stuff. Just watch out for those scary bugs, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: You can find all sorts of shiny things in the cavern.//If you dig deep enough, there are plenty of diamonds and stuff. Just watch out for those scary bugs, okay?

Text.SourceString: I’m just cleaning up a bit of moss on the stones.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m just cleaning up a bit of moss on the stones.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, I come here to read a book. It’s nice and quiet.//<portrait=normal>What are you, um, doing here?
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, I come here to read a book. It’s nice and quiet.//<portrait=normal>What are you, um, doing here?

Text.SourceString: Some of the books here are very odd.//<portrait=annoyed>I think I read something about a flying dog one time.
Text.LocalizedString: Some of the books here are very odd.//<portrait=annoyed>I think I read something about a flying dog one time.

Text.SourceString: It was probably <NPCName>Alice</>'s.//<portrait=normal>That girl is out of this world with her theories.
Text.LocalizedString: It was probably <NPCName>Alice</>'s.//<portrait=normal>That girl is out of this world with her theories.

Text.SourceString: If you're feeling tired, you can take a break upstairs. I tidied it up a bit earlier today.
Text.LocalizedString: If you're feeling tired, you can take a break upstairs. I tidied it up a bit earlier today.

Text.SourceString: I've got some work to take care of today, but it shouldn't take too long. After this, I'll head home, alright?
Text.LocalizedString: I've got some work to take care of today, but it shouldn't take too long. After this, I'll head home, alright?

Text.SourceString: Please be careful around the furnace, baby. I don't want you getting burned or anything.
Text.LocalizedString: Please be careful around the furnace, baby. I don't want you getting burned or anything.

Text.SourceString: Oh, uh... I came here for some tacos.//Do you want any, babe?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, uh... I came here for some tacos.//Do you want any, babe?

Text.SourceString: I’m going back to work after this.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going back to work after this.

Text.SourceString: It feels good to be outside every once in a while.//<portrait=normal>The shop is way too hot sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: It feels good to be outside every once in a while.//<portrait=normal>The shop is way too hot sometimes.

Text.SourceString: I don’t usually come here, but it’s <NPCName>Pablo</>'s birthday today, so I just came out for a celebratory meal.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t usually come here, but it’s <NPCName>Pablo</>'s birthday today, so I just came out for a celebratory meal.

Text.SourceString: I never noticed how loud it is in here. Wow!
Text.LocalizedString: I never noticed how loud it is in here. Wow!

Text.SourceString: I should go home soon. I feel exhausted.
Text.LocalizedString: I should go home soon. I feel exhausted.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Pablo</> and I went to the inn and had a quick dinner with our niece, <NPCName>Valentina</>, to celebrate her birthday last week.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Pablo</> and I went to the inn and had a quick dinner with our niece, <NPCName>Valentina</>, to celebrate her birthday last week.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Pablo</> gave her a geode because he thought she’d enjoy finding treasures, but I guess not…
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Pablo</> gave her a geode because he thought she’d enjoy finding treasures, but I guess not…

Text.SourceString: I might get new swimming trunks from <NPCName>Antonio’s</> shop.//<portrait=annoyed>Things are just so expensive there, though.
Text.LocalizedString: I might get new swimming trunks from <NPCName>Antonio’s</> shop.//<portrait=annoyed>Things are just so expensive there, though.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I can, um, come with you when you go to the cavern sometime.//<portrait=blushing>I can protect you, and you can mine in peace.//That way, you won’t get injured.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I can, um, come with you when you go to the cavern sometime.//<portrait=blushing>I can protect you, and you can mine in peace.//That way, you won’t get injured.

Text.SourceString: Don’t worry about me. I’ll be fine.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t worry about me. I’ll be fine.

Text.SourceString: I think I overworked myself yesterday.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I overworked myself yesterday.

Text.SourceString: Don’t worry, I wash this towel every day.//<portrait=normal>In this heat, you gotta.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t worry, I wash this towel every day.//<portrait=normal>In this heat, you gotta.

Text.SourceString: I saw <NpcName>Lily</> near the lake last week.//I see her there often, and usually she’s all alone. I hope things are okay with her.
Text.LocalizedString: I saw <NpcName>Lily</> near the lake last week.//I see her there often, and usually she’s all alone. I hope things are okay with her.

Text.SourceString: My cousin, <NpcName>Antonio</>, hooked me up with this jacket.//<portrait=normal>It’s hard to do my job in it, but the fabric feels really nice.
Text.LocalizedString: My cousin, <NpcName>Antonio</>, hooked me up with this jacket.//<portrait=normal>It’s hard to do my job in it, but the fabric feels really nice.

Text.SourceString: It feels weird, putting on a dress shirt, a jacket, and the whole shebang, but <NpcName>Antonio</> said it’s the style nowadays, so…//<portrait=happy>Mom said it makes me look fancy.
Text.LocalizedString: It feels weird, putting on a dress shirt, a jacket, and the whole shebang, but <NpcName>Antonio</> said it’s the style nowadays, so…//<portrait=happy>Mom said it makes me look fancy.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Valentina</> made me this beanie.//Can you see the tiny little bear on it? I love it.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Valentina</> made me this beanie.//Can you see the tiny little bear on it? I love it.

Text.SourceString: I like this jacket. It’s nice and warm.
Text.LocalizedString: I like this jacket. It’s nice and warm.
